From Peter Monta Subject Re MC SBI mixer Mark Musone writes any REALLY GOOD BOOKS on AM FM theory ALONG WITH DETAILED ELECTRICAL DIAGRAMS would help a I have seen a lot of theory books with no circuits and a lot of circuit books with no theory but one without the other does not Mixers have a wide variety of implementations the Mini Circuits part you mention is a doubly balanced diode mixer but active ones BJT FET seem more popular in consumer You might call MCL they have a nice The universal answer for wide coverage theory practice RF design is the ARRL Handbook published by the American Radio Relay League the radio amateur Any technical bookstore can order you The book is superb with lots of accessible theory construction projects and generally interesting You might also check out Solid State Design for the Radio Amateur I think by Hayward and someone This has sharper design and test information about subsystems like Peter Monta MIT Advanced Television Research Program